commit.message: Prepare changelog for 3.09 release.

Revert changes to shutdown and manual page that
would allow shutdown to force a reboot and send messages to firmware.

Revert "Correct documentation for -m flag."

This reverts commit 1c7bce8aa93bca0eca3c66884d1532a6b647f8d4.

Revert "On Linux systems, allow shutdown command to pass a message"

This reverts commit a5da21163d06495c56323e0414012f1166956f4b.

Make sure -m is properly documented in halt/reboot command and
triggers -f to enable a forced (in line) reboot.
Correct documentation for -m flag.

On Linux systems, allow shutdown command to pass a message
to the system firmware during the restart. This is
accomplished with the -m flag. It implies shutdown should call
a reboot itself, directly, rather than asking init to perform
the shutdown. This is usually not desired, but can be used
to pass parameters to the system firmware.
Merge branch '3.09' of https://github.com/slicer69/sysvinit into 3.09

Alow users to pass text to the system's firmware on Linux
when running the reboot command. This is accomplished with the
-m flag.

Added patch from kraj which allows hddown to compile when
musl is the C library on the system.

Patch for man/Makefile to fix the clean recipe.
Provided by Lucas Nussabaum and Mark Hindley
Updated changelog for release.

Applied a patch from floppm which adds kexec option to the halt command.

Updated halt documentation and help output to display parameters in
alphabetical order.

Floppym provided patch which causes the halt command
to call "shutdown -h -H" instead of "shutdown -h" when
halt is invoked without parameters. This forces the shutdown
command to set the INIT_HALT variable and assume, unless other
conditions apply, that the "halt" call really wants to halt the
machine and INIT_HALT should be set. In other words we
assume halt wants to halt unless told otherwise.
Addresses downstream Gentoo bug ID 911257.
Merge branch '3.07'
Merge branch '3.07' of https://github.com/slicer69/sysvinit into 3.07
Fixed typo

Accepted patch from Mark Hindley  which avoids clearing realpath information
in pidof when trying to find matching executables.

Accepted patch from Mark Hindle which avoids clearing realpath information
in pidof when trying to find matching executables.

Clarified pidof manual page to indicate pidof does not make multiple hops
through symbolic links.
Fixed memory initialization error in pidof. Fix provided by Markus Fischer.

pidof was not returning PIDs of programs which were launched
using a symbolic link. (ie /tmp/sleep when /tmp/sleep links to /usr/bin/sleep).
This is now fixed as we check both the realpath and symbolic path for processes.
In other words, "pidof /tmp/sleep" and "pidof /usr/bin/sleep" will return
the same PIDs when /tmp/sleep is a symbolic link to /usr/bin/sleep.

Fixed killall5 usage message to be more accurate. Command
can accept more than one parameter and that is now mentioned.

The killall5 command now avoids sending any signals,
including SIGSTOP and SIGCONT, to processes on the omit list.
Re-added man/po/pt.po translation file.
Reverted translation change which breaks build.
Re-adding original .po files.
Updated de.po file.
Fixed merge of translation files.
Fixed merge error.
